<p>I have read that using <code>&lt;c:out&gt;</code> tag will prevent XSS attacks but for some cases, say for example, displaying units with superscript (kg/m<sup>3</sup>) using c:out is displayed as plain text with sup tag (<code>kg/m&lt;sup&gt;3&lt;/sup&gt;)</code>. In order to display it properly, 'escapeXml=false' has to be used. </p>  <pre><code>&lt;c:out value="${units}" escapeXml="false&gt;&lt;/c:out&gt; </code></pre>  <p>But I was wondering whether using c:out tag with escapeXml=false is equivalent to not using c:out tag itself?</p>